WEBVTT

00:04.345 --> 00:06.136
[Krakow] Previously
on  Billions...

00:06.220 --> 00:07.762
I really need you
to come through for me now.

00:07.845 --> 00:09.261
Cuz I'm scared shitless.

00:09.345 --> 00:10.929
[Chuck] I'm sorry.
I didn't match.

00:11.011 --> 00:13.470
[Prince] Yonkers  is  you.
You are Yonkers.

00:13.553 --> 00:15.303
You stink
of the place.

00:15.387 --> 00:16.804
[Prince] And now you're
back in it.

00:16.887 --> 00:18.428
Before the funds land with us,

00:18.512 --> 00:20.720
we can designate them
to a public good.

00:20.804 --> 00:22.220
Like a law school clinic.

00:22.303 --> 00:26.136
I will do you the courtesy of
treating you like professionals.

00:26.220 --> 00:28.053
Do me the same.

00:28.136 --> 00:29.470
I'll have another.

00:29.553 --> 00:32.220
[Wags] I am not young,
but she will be.

00:32.303 --> 00:33.762
I want to know what
the rest of you can do

00:33.845 --> 00:35.303
to help make
this bank happen.

00:35.387 --> 00:36.720
[Taylor] There's
an opportunity here.

00:36.804 --> 00:38.136
We show him we are
where he should

00:38.220 --> 00:40.178
put his investable cash--
not into some bank.

00:40.261 --> 00:42.136
[Axe] The art world's been
good to me lately.

00:42.220 --> 00:43.804
It's gonna get me
my bank charter.

00:43.887 --> 00:46.762
But I need you to rip a letter
on my behalf out of the SEC

00:46.845 --> 00:48.136
and grease the skids
to a charter.

00:48.220 --> 00:50.053
For the original glamor shot?
Sure.

00:50.136 --> 00:52.553
Come on, man. I-I don't--
I don't do portraits.

00:52.637 --> 00:55.220
Well, I think we both
know otherwise.

00:55.303 --> 00:56.804
Since you're in there,

00:56.887 --> 00:59.303
maybe you can see when I can
expect some art out of him.

00:59.387 --> 01:00.220
We should all do dinner...

01:00.303 --> 01:02.512
[Axe] Me, you, Tanner.

01:02.595 --> 01:04.303
[Axe] Maybe I'll bring someone,
too...

01:04.387 --> 01:08.929
I know you meant no harm,
but harm is coming.

01:15.303 --> 01:18.303
♪ dramatic music  ♪

01:18.387 --> 01:22.178
♪♪♪

01:22.261 --> 01:25.970
♪♪♪

01:26.053 --> 01:29.387
Homemade sushi,
sashimi,

01:29.470 --> 01:31.387
and other small
Japanese bites.

01:31.470 --> 01:33.970
I sent Ryan to Japan
to stage around,

01:34.053 --> 01:36.387
and this is what
he came back with.

01:36.470 --> 01:38.887
Wow. I have been waiting
all day for this.

01:38.970 --> 01:40.053
To eat?

01:40.136 --> 01:42.053
He practices
intermittent fasting.

01:42.136 --> 01:43.762
I only eat in
an eight-hour stretch,

01:43.845 --> 01:45.887
and then I don't eat anything
for the other 16.

01:45.970 --> 01:47.887
Keeps my head clear
while I work.

01:47.970 --> 01:48.970
Flow state.

01:49.053 --> 01:50.553
Exactly.
You've tried it.

01:50.637 --> 01:53.804
I've tried it all:
Keto, fasting, gluten-free--

01:53.887 --> 01:55.261
I'm an intermittent eater,

01:55.345 --> 01:57.637
16 on, at least,
gluten-heavy.

01:57.720 --> 01:59.553
Ha. Also a way to go.

01:59.637 --> 02:01.512
I'll bear that diet in mind
for the reception.

02:01.595 --> 02:03.804
Why don't you just serve me,
fucking grilled?

02:03.887 --> 02:05.178
[Wags] Not a fan
of getting feted?

02:05.261 --> 02:06.553
[Tanner] Just
all the talk.

02:06.637 --> 02:08.095
He can't stand the buyers'--
what do you call it?

02:08.178 --> 02:10.220
"Bullshit interpretations."
Yeah.

02:10.303 --> 02:12.220
[Tanner] You know what question
really drives me insane--

02:12.303 --> 02:14.553
and it happens every
goddamned time is:

02:14.637 --> 02:15.929
"How do you know
when it's finished?"

02:16.011 --> 02:17.970
Well, sometimes
it's hard to tell--

02:18.053 --> 02:19.595
She's talking about
a Jackson Pollock

02:19.679 --> 02:21.428
we saw at gallery.
Yeah.

02:21.512 --> 02:24.178
Why not three splatters less,
or two more?

02:24.261 --> 02:26.053
That's what makes Pollock
Pollock, right?

02:26.136 --> 02:28.136
[Tanner] He can just stare
at it and say:

02:28.220 --> 02:30.845
[Tanner] "That's it.
It's complete. It's finished."

02:30.929 --> 02:33.220
That's what makes you
an artist.

02:33.303 --> 02:35.178
Otherwise,
you're nothing.

02:35.261 --> 02:37.428
I'm gonna have to be careful
when I talk to you.

02:37.512 --> 02:39.720
No, no, you need to engage
with artists and art

02:39.804 --> 02:41.095
and learn from it.

02:41.178 --> 02:42.428
This art stuff's
gonna be important

02:42.512 --> 02:44.178
later in our life together.

02:44.261 --> 02:46.762
A strong appreciation makes
for a well-rounded child.

02:46.845 --> 02:49.095
[clears throat]

02:49.178 --> 02:53.053
No--No real artist gives
a fuck about talk.

02:53.136 --> 02:55.970
They want you to look at
the work, understand it,

02:56.053 --> 02:58.345
and then jump out the window
without saying another word,

02:58.428 --> 03:00.804
because you never need to see
anything else ever again.

03:00.887 --> 03:03.637
What if it's a buyer
asking the questions?

03:03.720 --> 03:04.970
Same deal.

03:05.053 --> 03:08.887
Oh, the mythical
incorruptible artist.

03:08.970 --> 03:10.845
Impervious
to temptation.

03:10.929 --> 03:12.178
[Tanner laughs]

03:12.261 --> 03:14.845
If you buy me a ticket to Japan,
I'll go,

03:14.929 --> 03:16.387
but unlike your--
your cook,

03:16.470 --> 03:19.261
I-I can't promise you anything
for your trouble.

03:19.345 --> 03:20.720
[Wags] As long as you
came back inspired--

03:20.804 --> 03:23.387
Oh, this one
was born inspired.

03:23.470 --> 03:25.428
You should see him work.
It's insane.

03:25.512 --> 03:28.970
No, yeah, it must be
something to see.

03:29.053 --> 03:30.220
Oh, it is.

03:30.303 --> 03:32.095
He reminds me of
how you used to be--

03:32.178 --> 03:34.095
a guy doing what
he was born to do.

03:34.178 --> 03:35.679
Before I became
a burned-out hack?

03:35.762 --> 03:38.804
[chuckles] Don't put words
in my mouth.

03:38.887 --> 03:42.845
♪ jazz music  ♪

03:42.929 --> 03:44.303
You know what?

03:44.387 --> 03:48.512
All this talk of art
makes me want to see the work.

03:48.595 --> 03:50.178
I'll stop by tomorrow.

03:50.261 --> 03:52.595
Oh, no, I'm not ready
to show it.

03:52.679 --> 03:55.345
No, huh?

03:55.428 --> 03:58.178
♪♪♪

03:58.261 --> 04:00.970
♪♪♪

04:01.053 --> 04:03.845
Alright.
Well, you let me know.

04:03.929 --> 04:06.970
♪♪♪

04:07.053 --> 04:10.011
♪♪♪

04:10.095 --> 04:13.970
♪ dramatic music  ♪

04:14.053 --> 04:17.512
Welcome to the NYAG!

04:17.595 --> 04:19.303
Now, I feel no guilt
when I tell you all

04:19.387 --> 04:22.845
that I consider you
my smartest students.

04:22.929 --> 04:25.720
Oh, I'm sure that my colleagues
and I will all benefit greatly

04:25.804 --> 04:28.387
from the work of
your nimble legal minds.

04:28.470 --> 04:31.637
When I look out at you all,
I'm reminded of my younger self.

04:31.720 --> 04:34.136
And in the words of
your Billie Eilish,

04:34.220 --> 04:38.053
"The best of me,
the best of me is you."

04:38.136 --> 04:39.970
We know you must be
eager to get started,

04:40.053 --> 04:42.428
and we have an exciting
first assignment.

04:42.512 --> 04:46.011
Now: When it comes to the office
of the Attorney General,

04:46.095 --> 04:48.261
courage is a must.

04:48.345 --> 04:50.553
[Chuck] Courage to aim for
the highest targets

04:50.637 --> 04:52.345
without flinching.

04:52.428 --> 04:54.512
To brush away the dust from
the reticles on your scopes

04:54.595 --> 04:57.387
and take dead aim at even
the loftiest of our government.

04:57.470 --> 04:59.679
So today, you're gonna go after
a cabinet member.

04:59.762 --> 05:03.261
Yeah, Secretary of the Treasury,
Todd Krakow.

05:03.345 --> 05:05.136
We have records of his
every statement and action.

05:05.220 --> 05:07.387
[Sacker] Your task is
to build legal cases

05:07.470 --> 05:08.595
[Sacker] and arguments
against him.

05:08.679 --> 05:10.220
Let's find his lost tapes,

05:10.303 --> 05:14.053
his stained blue dress,
his perfect call.

05:14.136 --> 05:15.762
Let's get to work!

05:15.845 --> 05:19.387
♪♪♪

05:19.470 --> 05:21.261
-[Wags] Yes!
-[Axe] Yes! Come on!

05:21.345 --> 05:23.345
-[Axe] Oh, yeah!
-[Wags] Fucking yes!

05:23.428 --> 05:24.762
[Axe] You can fucking smell
that fucking...

05:24.845 --> 05:28.428
That may sound like a joyous
Kwanzaa celebration to you--

05:28.512 --> 05:30.136
Kwanzaa was last--
Well, it ain't the sounds of

05:30.220 --> 05:34.095
a goddamned Chanukah festival
of lights either.

05:34.178 --> 05:37.053
Or the motherfucking eve of
motherfucking Christmas--

05:37.136 --> 05:39.303
I really don't think you want
that phrase on the record,

05:39.387 --> 05:41.887
-there are HR considera--
-No.

05:41.970 --> 05:46.095
What that sound is,
is a funeral dirge.

05:46.178 --> 05:49.470
And that funeral
is ours.

05:49.553 --> 05:51.470
[Dollar Bill] That cheering
is for Krakow

05:51.553 --> 05:53.470
[Dollar Bill] rubber stamping
Axe's federal bank charter.

05:53.553 --> 05:55.679
It's really happening?
Happened.

05:55.762 --> 05:58.095
Fast tracking it...

05:58.178 --> 06:01.011
Now, I joined the party
when I first heard about

06:01.095 --> 06:02.637
us becoming a bank...

06:02.720 --> 06:05.095
Because
it sounded sturdy.

06:05.178 --> 06:07.470
Secure. Lucrative.

06:07.553 --> 06:08.970
But the more
I researched--

06:09.053 --> 06:11.804
Yeah.
The worse it fucking is.

06:11.887 --> 06:13.303
Man the turrets

06:13.387 --> 06:15.553
and start loosing ordnance
on whatever you see.

06:15.637 --> 06:17.970
Because it's gonna be
eat what you kill soon enough.

06:18.053 --> 06:19.970
Wait, are you hunting
or at war?

06:20.053 --> 06:22.512
Both.
As you all better be.

06:22.595 --> 06:25.303
We're going to have to
deregister as a hedge fund.

06:25.387 --> 06:28.095
This place will become
a family office,

06:28.178 --> 06:30.553
to separate commerce
from banking.

06:30.637 --> 06:33.095
No outside fees to
cover our salaries.

06:33.178 --> 06:34.970
Redundancies will
become clear.

06:35.053 --> 06:36.845
To him.

06:36.929 --> 06:38.595
Some of us
will be Midsommar'd.

06:38.679 --> 06:40.637
Yes! Exactly!

06:40.720 --> 06:43.011
I don't actually know what
that means, but it sounds--

06:43.095 --> 06:44.845
Horrible.
Utterly horrible.

06:44.929 --> 06:47.845
Axe, um...

06:47.929 --> 06:49.512
If we do...

06:49.595 --> 06:51.887
When we do get
the bank charter,

06:51.970 --> 06:53.720
how much are
our lives changing?

06:53.804 --> 06:54.720
Will our jobs--

06:54.804 --> 06:55.970
No, it's not a problem.

06:56.053 --> 06:57.845
[Tuk] It's not?

06:57.929 --> 06:59.679
Well, it's not
my  problem.

06:59.762 --> 07:01.136
And don't ask another guy
about your future.

07:01.220 --> 07:03.512
Make your own
fucking future.

07:03.595 --> 07:06.428
It's like my own mother took
the form of your body.

07:06.512 --> 07:08.095
I can almost taste
her ggori gomtang.

07:08.178 --> 07:09.970
It's chilling...

07:10.053 --> 07:12.804
[Ben Kim] But, we have all been
through so much together.

07:12.887 --> 07:14.428
[Ben Kim] Lean
and fat times.

07:14.512 --> 07:16.470
We always come through
at Axe Capital.

07:16.553 --> 07:18.470
Is this an overcorrection
to conditions?

07:18.553 --> 07:19.637
[Ben Kim] Shouldn't we
just ride it out?

07:19.720 --> 07:21.220
Fucking right we should.

07:21.303 --> 07:23.428
As the Pittsburgh
Steelers do.

07:23.512 --> 07:25.804
And that consistency
has served them well.

07:25.887 --> 07:28.178
Best-run franchise in--
Second best.

07:28.261 --> 07:29.804
Like Coach Belichick says:

07:29.887 --> 07:31.929
You wait till halftime before
you start making adjustments,

07:32.011 --> 07:34.595
it's too fucking late...

07:38.804 --> 07:40.553
Change is scary.

07:40.637 --> 07:42.428
I know.

07:42.512 --> 07:45.303
But this is gonna be
better for all of you.

07:46.970 --> 07:48.970
Maybe not all of you.

07:49.053 --> 07:52.095
♪ dramatic music  ♪

07:52.178 --> 07:56.929
♪♪♪

07:57.011 --> 08:01.762
♪♪♪

08:01.845 --> 08:04.845
You know I didn't really say
what I feel down there.

08:04.929 --> 08:06.303
If I said what
I really believed--

08:06.387 --> 08:07.804
Boss. I know what
you were thinking.

08:07.887 --> 08:09.720
It was pellucid without
you even saying it.

08:09.804 --> 08:11.136
Like I was hearing
your thoughts.

08:11.220 --> 08:12.720
Really?
What was I--

08:12.804 --> 08:14.720
You just wanted
your fucking coffee

08:14.804 --> 08:16.929
and couldn't believe the
weakness you were witnessing.

08:17.011 --> 08:19.762
You were also thinking about the
16 trades we made this morning,

08:19.845 --> 08:22.470
and, at one point, I saw you
look toward the front desk,

08:22.553 --> 08:24.261
and calculate the value
relative to cost

08:24.345 --> 08:25.679
of having two
receptionists there.

08:25.762 --> 08:28.345
What kind of Derren Brown
mindreader bullshit is this?

08:28.428 --> 08:29.804
It's not bullshit.

08:29.887 --> 08:31.095
It's this...

08:31.178 --> 08:32.720
Vigilantrix.

08:32.804 --> 08:34.804
Our next big play.

08:34.887 --> 08:37.136
We are not a bank
quite yet.

08:37.220 --> 08:39.512
And we may as well fucking
crush it one more time

08:39.595 --> 08:40.845
before we become one.

08:40.929 --> 08:43.470
This drug, Axe,
it's the killer app

08:43.553 --> 08:45.095
in the pharma space
you've been chasing.

08:45.178 --> 08:48.178
It's a focus ratchet,
a productivity booster.

08:48.261 --> 08:51.136
The audience at a pharma
conference got one to try.

08:51.220 --> 08:53.637
But after I had a taste,
I copped the whole box.

08:53.720 --> 08:55.470
Vigilantrix.

08:55.553 --> 08:57.387
I read about the trials.

08:57.470 --> 08:59.303
That's the thing, huh?

08:59.387 --> 09:01.595
It sure is.
It's the Limitless  shit.

09:01.679 --> 09:03.679
It's got me firing
on all--

09:03.762 --> 09:07.261
it's giving me crazy
mental clarity and acuity.

09:07.345 --> 09:08.762
I'm even using words
like "acuity."

09:08.845 --> 09:11.011
And "pellucid,"
yeah, I heard.

09:11.095 --> 09:12.303
[Victor] The stuff works.

09:12.387 --> 09:13.470
If it's got me
thinking like you,

09:13.553 --> 09:17.220
imagine who it'll have
you thinking like.

09:17.303 --> 09:22.011
♪♪♪

09:22.095 --> 09:26.970
♪♪♪

09:27.053 --> 09:31.679
♪♪♪

