19:09.553 --> 19:10.970
[knock on door]

19:11.053 --> 19:12.887
[door opens]

19:12.970 --> 19:15.762
Good to see you
again, Wendy.

19:15.845 --> 19:19.095
And you, Taylor.
Lauren, your rep precedes.

19:19.178 --> 19:20.762
Now, how are we gonna
disarm this bomb

19:20.845 --> 19:23.637
before it blows up
in our faces?

19:23.720 --> 19:25.303
Please have a seat.

19:27.929 --> 19:31.095
Maybe we need to throw it
over a cliff before it does.

19:31.178 --> 19:32.261
[chuckles]

19:32.345 --> 19:33.804
I used to love those cartoons

19:33.887 --> 19:35.512
where the coyote
would get his fingers caught

19:35.595 --> 19:37.428
in the bomb
right as he released it.

19:37.512 --> 19:40.804
He'd blow up and then be back to
himself after the commercial.

19:40.887 --> 19:42.303
Reconstituted.
But we...

19:42.387 --> 19:43.804
Yes. Mortal.

19:43.887 --> 19:47.220
Once we blow up,
no reconstitution possible.

19:47.303 --> 19:49.804
So I, too, want to avoid
an explosion here.

19:49.887 --> 19:51.345
We'll listen to
any plan you may have,

19:51.428 --> 19:53.345
but we remain unsure
if we're taking part.

19:53.428 --> 19:56.261
Until such time as it's clear
our agendas are aligned, anyway.

19:56.345 --> 19:58.136
What do you see
as first steps?

19:58.220 --> 20:00.095
We need to
re-source the tin.

20:00.178 --> 20:02.011
Yes. But we can't
be noisy about it.

20:02.095 --> 20:03.970
I'd propose a year-long
transition plan.

20:04.053 --> 20:05.804
To a new source.
That we sell the board on.

20:05.887 --> 20:07.303
And we slow down
order fulfillment,

20:07.387 --> 20:08.595
so we don't sell any more--

20:08.679 --> 20:09.970
Good. In theory.

20:10.053 --> 20:11.887
If we can ensure that
the story of the scandal

20:11.970 --> 20:12.845
doesn't get to the press.

20:12.929 --> 20:14.470
What about board members
leaking?

20:14.553 --> 20:16.387
That's a real risk.
Who are you worried about?

20:16.470 --> 20:18.303
Not sure.
I was hoping you could

20:18.387 --> 20:20.553
profile them to determine
who might crack...

20:20.637 --> 20:25.470
♪ dramatic music  ♪

20:25.553 --> 20:28.512
Look, I know you said
you're not sure if you're in,

20:28.595 --> 20:31.178
but it feels like we're already
rowing in the same direction.

20:31.261 --> 20:32.679
And we have a conference room
you can work in

20:32.762 --> 20:34.303
[Scooter] before we have to
call the board back.

20:34.387 --> 20:38.637
♪♪♪

20:38.720 --> 20:40.053
Okay.

20:40.136 --> 20:41.345
We're on it.

20:43.929 --> 20:46.428
[breathes deeply]

20:50.261 --> 20:52.345
[Chuck] Thanks for
coming down, Pete.

20:52.428 --> 20:54.470
Much as I hate being here,
I figured I should show up

20:54.553 --> 20:57.637
[Decker] and avoid the subpoena
sure to follow.

20:57.720 --> 21:00.053
Wise choice.

21:00.136 --> 21:02.345
Now I know
you've gone well beyond

21:02.428 --> 21:04.428
selling memberships
at your robo-gym,

21:04.512 --> 21:08.387
into the physical-transformation
through-science space.

21:08.470 --> 21:10.720
Specifically, that
you're helping athletes

21:10.804 --> 21:14.220
boost performance--
and beat drug tests.

21:14.303 --> 21:16.679
Hold on a sec,
I never, never, ever--

21:16.762 --> 21:18.053
Let's not.

21:18.136 --> 21:19.762
If you didn't,
you wouldn't be here.

21:19.845 --> 21:24.553
And [chuckles]
I wouldn't need you.

21:24.637 --> 21:27.011
Need me to what?

21:27.095 --> 21:29.261
Put me with a certain type
of doctor that can help out

21:29.345 --> 21:31.804
with a family member's
kidney situation.

21:34.345 --> 21:35.887
Where are we at exactly?

21:35.970 --> 21:40.220
Well, uh, it seems my father
wasn't healthy enough

21:40.303 --> 21:42.387
to pass the workup
to get on the donor list.

21:42.470 --> 21:46.553
Oh. They always try to pick off
the least viable.

21:46.637 --> 21:50.595
So step one is getting
your dad's numbers

21:50.679 --> 21:52.053
[Decker] to where he can
get on that list.

21:52.136 --> 21:53.178
Uh-huh.

21:53.261 --> 21:56.220
But it's a long wait.
Years--

21:56.303 --> 21:58.220
Yeah.
Up to five years.

21:58.303 --> 22:00.804
And that is a death sentence
for him.

22:00.887 --> 22:03.261
Which brings us to part two:

22:03.345 --> 22:06.762
If I can't
move him up the list,

22:06.845 --> 22:08.387
once you get him on it,

22:08.470 --> 22:13.345
I need you to
locate me a donor.

22:16.387 --> 22:18.929
Shit. Okay.

22:19.011 --> 22:21.804
Murky waters.

22:24.595 --> 22:28.887
[clears throat]
But I have a guy.

22:30.887 --> 22:32.845
He's a-a "doctor"--

22:32.929 --> 22:34.387
[Chuck] An MD?

22:34.470 --> 22:37.303
Does he still
have an MD?

22:37.387 --> 22:39.470
Did Hippocrates
have one?

22:39.553 --> 22:41.136
You want to put me
on the stand

22:41.220 --> 22:43.053
or you want me
to fix your dad?

22:43.136 --> 22:44.762
My guy's the right man
for the job.

22:44.845 --> 22:46.970
EPO, platelets,
clean this, clean that.

22:47.053 --> 22:48.929
[Decker] He'll tune your pops up
like a Stradivarius,

22:49.011 --> 22:51.095
[Decker] so he passes the test
to get on that list.

22:51.178 --> 22:53.637
And he could
find you an organ.

22:53.720 --> 22:55.804
Good.
That's just what I need.

22:55.887 --> 22:58.595
I want to meet ASAP.

22:58.679 --> 23:00.762
I'll arrange it.

23:00.845 --> 23:03.428
$5,000, up front.
Cash.

23:03.512 --> 23:04.887
This guy don't take
Blue Cross.

23:04.970 --> 23:07.762
[laughing] Okay.
I see.

23:07.845 --> 23:10.136
And what's your piece
of that?

23:10.220 --> 23:13.095
Piece? Me?

23:13.178 --> 23:14.887
I'm just here to help.

23:14.970 --> 23:19.345
♪ dramatic music  ♪

23:19.428 --> 23:22.136
Let's go, gimme what you got,
hit me hard--

23:22.220 --> 23:24.428
So, I didn't know what you meant
by 'grab the rock' before,

23:24.512 --> 23:27.136
but now I do, and I have to say
it's brilliant--

23:27.220 --> 23:29.053
Right--
I mean a tech and aerospace play

23:29.136 --> 23:30.845
that can harvest one
mid-size meteor--

23:30.929 --> 23:33.053
And the yield would be--
Fucking outsized--

23:33.136 --> 23:35.095
So, I think I'm seeing
the macro play:

23:35.178 --> 23:36.512
cornering the rare mineral
market--

23:36.595 --> 23:38.053
Bam.

23:38.136 --> 23:39.178
Beyond gold and platinum,

23:39.261 --> 23:40.512
we're talking cobalt,

23:40.595 --> 23:42.345
tungsten, rhodium--
Right--

23:42.428 --> 23:44.095
We'll control production
on every cellphone

23:44.178 --> 23:45.887
from now until--
Till they're fucking obsolete.

23:45.970 --> 23:48.679
Space-X, Blue Origin,
Virgin Galactic--

23:48.762 --> 23:50.470
and all their
feeder tech.

23:50.553 --> 23:52.136
Lots of opportunity to roll up
a strong ground game--

23:52.220 --> 23:53.345
And speaking of ground game,

23:53.428 --> 23:55.303
we've got to bring in
the geo-political piece.

23:55.387 --> 23:57.637
Chile. Big things happening in
their political landscape--

23:57.720 --> 23:59.220
If their election tilts the way
it looks like--

23:59.303 --> 24:00.637
pro-mining,
pro-business--

24:00.720 --> 24:02.095
we're talking about a base,

24:02.178 --> 24:04.053
with massive government
incentives,

24:04.136 --> 24:05.720
good launch sites,
strategic partnerships--

24:05.804 --> 24:07.845
that'll make this
whole thing go.

24:07.929 --> 24:10.512
Liquidity.
We need it.

24:10.595 --> 24:12.553
We should dump out of
$3, $3.2 billion worth

24:12.637 --> 24:15.095
of our other positions
in order to free up capital

24:15.178 --> 24:16.387
for the mineral play.

24:16.470 --> 24:18.053
It'll be more than
fucking worth it.

24:18.136 --> 24:19.387
Say the word
and I'll come out of the chute

24:19.470 --> 24:21.553
like the German bobsled team
at Lake Placid.

24:21.637 --> 24:23.136
Word. I said it.
Go do it.

24:23.220 --> 24:26.220
♪ up-tempo music  ♪

24:26.303 --> 24:29.428
♪♪♪

24:29.512 --> 24:32.762
♪♪♪

24:35.011 --> 24:37.929
You ever see the show
The Good Doctor,  Chuck?

24:38.011 --> 24:39.470
Can't say I have.

24:39.553 --> 24:41.887
Well, he's a-a great
and feeling young man,

24:41.970 --> 24:44.470
despite this outer affect
that would suggest otherwise.

24:44.553 --> 24:47.303
And he's without
a care for money.

24:47.387 --> 24:49.428
And the good doctor here
is the same?

24:49.512 --> 24:51.136
Nope.
Dead opposite.

24:51.220 --> 24:52.804
I did that "care for the
patient" thing for years.

24:52.887 --> 24:54.053
But they kept suing me,
the fuckers.

24:54.136 --> 24:55.553
Now, they can
fuck themselves,

24:55.637 --> 24:57.053
unless they're willing
to pay me to unfuck them.

24:57.136 --> 25:01.345
But where this man,
Dr. Swerdlow,

25:01.428 --> 25:03.261
and the Good Doc
are similar is:

25:03.345 --> 25:06.261
They both are excellent
practitioners of their crafts.

25:06.345 --> 25:07.470
And mine is: to get men
like your father--

25:07.553 --> 25:10.053
worthy paying customers--
exactly what they need,

25:10.136 --> 25:11.887
before it's too fucking late.
Still saving lives.

25:11.970 --> 25:13.428
But getting me some
beach houses on the side,

25:13.512 --> 25:15.095
ya know what I'm saying,
baby girl?

25:15.178 --> 25:17.303
See? I told him not to
pretend to care, Chuck,

25:17.387 --> 25:18.970
that you wouldn't--
you wouldn't go for that.

25:19.053 --> 25:20.762
Certainly not. No.

25:20.845 --> 25:23.720
Not a chance. No way.
Okay. Good. Got it.

25:23.804 --> 25:26.136
So. What's the actual
way this happens?

25:26.220 --> 25:28.428
Well, this meeting
is $5,000 cash.

25:28.512 --> 25:31.053
That happens now.

25:42.553 --> 25:44.804
Okay, here's how
we fix this thing.

25:44.887 --> 25:48.345
Fix meaning repair, but also
fix meaning rig the system.

25:48.428 --> 25:49.804
Why say that part
out loud?

25:49.887 --> 25:51.470
Cuz it's fun.

25:51.553 --> 25:53.679
What we'll do, once your payment
is complete, is run a course:

25:53.762 --> 25:56.220
Platelets for red cell count,
blood pressure meds,

25:56.303 --> 25:58.887
something to improve his
glomerular filtration rate--

25:58.970 --> 26:01.011
and I'm not just talking about
fucking around with Bardoxolone.

26:01.095 --> 26:02.512
I've got some special shit
from Mexico City

26:02.595 --> 26:04.679
that'll really do
the fucking job.

26:04.762 --> 26:07.679
Oh, and also a clean urine
deposit before his next exam.

26:07.762 --> 26:11.095
Uh-huh. And how is that, uh,
particular deposit made?

26:11.178 --> 26:13.011
With a special turkey baster,
right up his cock.

26:13.095 --> 26:14.679
Okay.
If this shit backfires,

26:14.762 --> 26:18.887
and my dad dies of an infection
caused by this rug merchant,

26:18.970 --> 26:19.970
I'm coming for you.

26:20.053 --> 26:21.512
I know.
Yet I'm here.

26:21.595 --> 26:23.470
Which should tell you
the level of my faith.

26:23.553 --> 26:26.512
So, after all this,
if my other moves don't work,

26:26.595 --> 26:28.679
and I can't jump him to
the front of the queue--

26:28.762 --> 26:31.220
how do we secure an organ?

26:31.303 --> 26:33.595
You mean the kidney itself?
Mm.

26:36.095 --> 26:38.720
That puppy comes from
this pupp-ette right here.

26:40.845 --> 26:44.345
She's an illegal just over
from El Salvador. And a match.

26:44.428 --> 26:46.470
She'll be out
of lockup soon.

26:46.553 --> 26:47.887
And she's willing
to sell one.

26:47.970 --> 26:49.136
In fact,
she almost already did,

26:49.220 --> 26:51.303
but the fucker
croaked too soon.

26:51.387 --> 26:53.970
She'll do anything it takes
for the 38K it pays.

26:54.053 --> 26:55.303
[Swerdlow] Influx at
the southern border

26:55.387 --> 26:57.053
[Swerdlow] isn't
all that bad.

26:57.136 --> 26:59.720
Lots of desperate people
willing to sell their parts.

26:59.804 --> 27:01.053
She wants to do this!

27:01.136 --> 27:02.804
Even I can't do it.

27:06.136 --> 27:07.595
Is there
any alternative?

27:07.679 --> 27:09.720
Oh, shit, yeah. I can change
gears like an Aston Martin

27:09.804 --> 27:12.136
with paddles on the steering
wheel--fast and smooth.

27:12.220 --> 27:13.428
For the right price,

27:13.512 --> 27:14.804
I can get your old man
in a scratch and dent.

27:14.887 --> 27:16.553
Okay. Maybe we've covered
enough the day--

27:16.637 --> 27:18.553
No. You brought the man here,
let him speak.

27:18.637 --> 27:20.679
Let the man speak.

27:20.762 --> 27:23.762
Diseased donor, Chuck.
Hep C. HIV.

27:23.845 --> 27:25.929
[Decker] These people need
money. They're willing to share.

27:26.011 --> 27:28.095
[Decker] And then we treat your
dad for the underlying problems.

27:28.178 --> 27:29.762
No. Heard enough.
More than enough.

27:29.845 --> 27:31.887
Might have to
box my ears after this

27:31.970 --> 27:34.428
so the ringing replaces
your fucking words.

27:34.512 --> 27:36.595
I'll just take my cash back,
please,

27:36.679 --> 27:38.845
and we'll all go on
with our lives.

27:38.929 --> 27:41.345
No refunds!

27:45.679 --> 27:47.887
Look, Charlie,

27:47.970 --> 27:50.720
your reaction
is normal, usual.

27:50.804 --> 27:53.345
But you will
reflect upon this.

27:53.428 --> 27:55.679
If times get
desperate enough,

27:55.762 --> 27:59.095
which they will,
you'll call me.

27:59.178 --> 28:00.970
They usually
end up calling me.

28:01.053 --> 28:03.136
Always.

28:03.220 --> 28:04.887
They always call.

28:04.970 --> 28:06.970
♪ dramatic music  ♪

28:07.053 --> 28:09.136
[keyboards clacking]

28:09.220 --> 28:12.011
♪♪♪

28:12.095 --> 28:15.136
♪♪♪

28:17.011 --> 28:18.970
I've profiled
the board members.

28:19.053 --> 28:20.470
Vargas is
fucking wobbly.

28:20.553 --> 28:21.679
She'll need to be bought off

28:21.762 --> 28:23.470
or taped up
in bubble wrap--

28:23.553 --> 28:25.303
otherwise she'll spill to
management or to the press.

28:25.387 --> 28:26.720
Or both.

28:30.136 --> 28:31.720
Alright,
I changed my mind--

28:31.804 --> 28:33.887
or I've come to another state
of mind, based on your work.

28:33.970 --> 28:36.804
I applied the five-year,
50,000-foot test.

28:36.887 --> 28:40.345
I looked at our decision
from above and from the future.

28:42.136 --> 28:43.470
And?

28:43.553 --> 28:44.679
No slow transition.

28:44.762 --> 28:46.345
We can't let
another day pass

28:46.428 --> 28:48.720
with this company buying
conflict minerals.

28:48.804 --> 28:52.595
The story will leak,
as you say--as it always does.

28:52.679 --> 28:55.011
Then, even with
what we're planning,

28:55.095 --> 28:57.595
the company will be
gutted by regulators

28:57.679 --> 28:59.011
and the stock price
with it.

28:59.095 --> 29:00.220
So we break the story
immediately

29:00.303 --> 29:01.553
and halt all production.

29:01.637 --> 29:03.512
And we use the new
clean tin source.

29:03.595 --> 29:04.679
Even though
it won't start up

29:04.762 --> 29:06.512
and get to capacity
for six to seven months.

29:06.595 --> 29:09.053
Long term this may be
the way to a big win, but...

29:09.136 --> 29:10.428
Yeah, I know.

29:10.512 --> 29:12.345
The company will take
a catastrophic loss

29:12.428 --> 29:15.762
for the next three
to four quarters.

29:15.845 --> 29:20.011
Look, I don't expect you two to
take this bumpy ride with me...

29:22.053 --> 29:26.470
...so I'll buy Mase Carbon out
of its position in the company.

29:26.553 --> 29:28.136
It's only fair.

29:28.220 --> 29:30.011
Whoa.

29:30.095 --> 29:31.679
There's the Mike Prince
I was warned about.

29:31.762 --> 29:33.261
Did you stunt
this entire thing?

29:33.345 --> 29:36.387
Was that supply chain guy
just in a box at your office?

29:36.470 --> 29:39.095
Look, I can see how
it looks like a move--

29:39.178 --> 29:40.720
but I'm not making one.

29:40.804 --> 29:42.387
Did you gin up a different
solution to this thing

29:42.470 --> 29:44.595
to come out a winner while
we were sitting here working?

29:44.679 --> 29:46.762
Is that what's behind
your sudden interest

29:46.845 --> 29:48.804
in buying our shares?

29:50.929 --> 29:53.261
I get why a life spent
working by Axe's side

29:53.345 --> 29:54.387
would make you ask.

29:54.470 --> 29:56.887
But no,
it's a genuine offer,

29:56.970 --> 29:58.679
because
you threw in with me.

29:58.762 --> 30:00.387
The way my company
is structured,

30:00.470 --> 30:01.845
I can afford to
grind it out for a while.

30:01.929 --> 30:04.053
I know you're
built differently.

30:04.136 --> 30:05.637
But, heck,
if you don't trust me,

30:05.720 --> 30:07.220
you can buy
my position out.

30:07.303 --> 30:09.679
That's a story that doesn't
hurt the company.

30:09.762 --> 30:12.095
Or we can share.

30:12.178 --> 30:13.887
You make the call.

30:13.970 --> 30:17.428
I just want what's best
for the solar space.

30:17.512 --> 30:20.470
♪♪♪

30:20.553 --> 30:21.595
I believe him.

30:21.679 --> 30:23.095
Me too.

30:23.178 --> 30:26.470
Don't buy us out.
We won't buy you out.

30:26.553 --> 30:27.887
We'll ride together.
We'll stay in the company

30:27.970 --> 30:29.595
and take the bumps and bruises
along with you.

30:29.679 --> 30:30.845
It's the right thing to do,

30:30.929 --> 30:33.679
and it will, eventually,
become profitable again.

30:33.762 --> 30:36.011
Not many can play
the long game.

30:36.095 --> 30:37.929
I'm impressed.

30:38.011 --> 30:39.428
[elevator bell dings]

30:42.595 --> 30:44.929
Oh! Welcome.
Thank you for coming.

30:45.011 --> 30:47.553
Donna will show you
where to set up.

30:51.637 --> 30:52.804
Blood drive!

30:52.887 --> 30:54.136
Blood bank is here.

30:54.220 --> 30:56.970
Stop in, get typed
and donate, huh?

30:58.220 --> 30:59.762
I have the material
from the Yale group.

30:59.845 --> 31:01.970
Mm.

31:02.053 --> 31:03.970
Hmm.

31:05.303 --> 31:06.804
Nothing very chewy...

31:06.887 --> 31:08.595
No. Not going to get
Krakow out of office.

31:08.679 --> 31:12.095
Nothing that'll stick.
So we have to...

31:14.095 --> 31:15.470
If we can't take him out,

31:15.553 --> 31:17.470
we have to make him
take himself out.

31:17.553 --> 31:20.178
The old
B3 bomber trick?

31:20.261 --> 31:22.136
The last great Mamet.
And yes.

31:22.220 --> 31:23.595
That's exactly it.

31:23.679 --> 31:26.136
"Secretary Krakow,
we cannot confirm

31:26.220 --> 31:27.762
the investigation
into corruption,

31:27.845 --> 31:29.595
nor your role in same."

31:29.679 --> 31:30.804
Yeah.
That'll work on him.

31:30.887 --> 31:33.345
[chuckles]
Especially him.

31:33.428 --> 31:36.845
He's in town for
an economic advisory panel

31:36.929 --> 31:38.470
at the New York Fed.

31:38.553 --> 31:41.095
Invite him over.
ASAP.

31:44.345 --> 31:47.428
What's behind the forced
audience in the outer borough?

31:47.512 --> 31:49.428
Beyond the chance to catch up,
you mean?

31:49.512 --> 31:52.136
[chuckles]
Uh, well,

31:52.220 --> 31:55.011
I want to tell you

31:55.095 --> 31:58.887
that I can't confirm
the investigation.

31:58.970 --> 32:01.011
What investigation?

32:01.095 --> 32:04.011
There is none.
I'm sure.

32:04.095 --> 32:06.345
[chuckles]

32:06.428 --> 32:09.553
I mean,
I am not saying that

32:09.637 --> 32:13.095
they're looking into those
tax shelters of yours--

32:13.178 --> 32:15.387
Of mine?!

32:15.470 --> 32:16.553
Or those cap gains--

32:16.637 --> 32:17.845
Yeah, no, okay.

32:17.929 --> 32:20.470
What I'm--
What I'm trying to say is:

32:20.553 --> 32:23.220
I can't let on,

32:23.303 --> 32:24.512
officially,

32:24.595 --> 32:26.720
that it isn't.

32:26.804 --> 32:28.303
Probably nothing.

32:28.387 --> 32:29.553
Mm.

32:29.637 --> 32:31.387
If we were to
officially tell you

32:31.470 --> 32:32.762
that there were
a probe--

32:32.845 --> 32:35.887
Oh, Christ,
there's a probe.

32:35.970 --> 32:36.970
He's a friendly.

32:38.637 --> 32:40.220
If there were a probe,

32:40.303 --> 32:42.387
it would be against
federal officials

32:42.470 --> 32:45.845
using their positions
for illegal personal gain.

32:45.929 --> 32:48.053
Good thing I don't
traffic in that.

32:48.136 --> 32:49.679
No, of course.

32:49.762 --> 32:51.637
But, shit...

32:51.720 --> 32:54.553
Who have they gotten to?
What level?

32:54.637 --> 32:56.720
We don't have names,

32:56.804 --> 32:58.512
just cabinet level, though.

33:02.178 --> 33:04.261
Cabinet level!

33:04.345 --> 33:06.553
Trust no one.

33:06.637 --> 33:09.261
And think about
how this will play.

33:09.345 --> 33:11.011
If you're around
any of this conduct,

33:11.095 --> 33:13.261
you need to stand up
for your integrity--

33:13.345 --> 33:17.929
loudly--and condemn any illegal
moves by your colleagues--

33:18.011 --> 33:19.804
so it's clear when
the tapes are heard.

33:19.887 --> 33:22.887
♪ dramatic music  ♪

33:22.970 --> 33:27.053
♪♪♪

33:27.136 --> 33:28.720
I appreciate
the warning.

33:28.804 --> 33:32.470
♪♪♪

33:32.553 --> 33:36.470
♪♪♪

33:36.553 --> 33:38.136
How many languages
do you have?

33:38.220 --> 33:39.887
Python, Java of course.

33:39.970 --> 33:41.637
I can also do stuff
in JSFuck.

33:41.720 --> 33:44.178
And I used to dick around with
Malbolge, but just for fun.

33:44.261 --> 33:46.428
No. Spoken languages.
Not programming.

33:46.512 --> 33:47.762
Even though that's hot
in a different way

33:47.845 --> 33:49.428
at a different time

33:49.512 --> 33:51.553
and when an entirely different
person is telling me.

33:51.637 --> 33:53.387
Just English.
[Rian] Weirdest thing.

33:53.470 --> 33:54.970
This stuff--I am
suddenly remembering

33:55.053 --> 33:56.637
all the Spanish I took
in high school.

33:56.720 --> 33:59.095
I'm banging through language
proficiency tests on here.

33:59.178 --> 34:02.720
I think I will be officially
bilingual in like an hour.

34:02.804 --> 34:06.303
♪ up-tempo music  ♪

34:06.387 --> 34:07.637
I'm going to work in there.

34:07.720 --> 34:08.887
For optimal focus.

34:08.970 --> 34:10.887
That's impressive.
I'm impressed.

34:10.970 --> 34:12.553
I already was impressed by you,
and this'll--

34:12.637 --> 34:13.929
Yeah. I know.

34:14.011 --> 34:15.303
I see how you stare.

34:15.387 --> 34:16.512
I don't stare.

34:16.595 --> 34:19.053
I look sometimes.
Just look.

34:19.136 --> 34:21.595
Look turns into a stare
after like 20 seconds.

34:21.679 --> 34:23.845
15. Quince.

34:23.929 --> 34:25.720
[chuckles]

34:25.804 --> 34:28.053
You know, they say
you're truly bilingual

34:28.136 --> 34:30.220
when you can dream
in the other language.

34:30.303 --> 34:32.470
I can't wait to find out.

34:32.553 --> 34:34.512
[chuckles]

34:34.595 --> 34:39.345
♪♪♪

34:39.428 --> 34:41.470
Yeah, I think that'll benefit
the most people--

34:41.553 --> 34:42.929
Absolutely.
The whole idea of easing

34:43.011 --> 34:44.261
is to allow credit
to flow to those who--

34:44.345 --> 34:47.136
Yes. That's why we have to
approve this--

34:47.220 --> 34:50.053
hey, can we pause the
note-taking for a second?

34:50.136 --> 34:53.261
Jim, been meaning to tell you
I worked it out

34:53.345 --> 34:56.220
for you to jump on the Mesa-Comm
board when your term is over.

34:56.303 --> 34:58.303
[laughter]

35:02.553 --> 35:04.553
[laughs]

35:04.637 --> 35:06.720
[train rattling]

35:13.679 --> 35:15.053
[man laughs]

35:15.136 --> 35:18.136
[rattling continues]

35:22.679 --> 35:24.512
I won't have it!

35:24.595 --> 35:25.929
I won't be party to it!

35:26.011 --> 35:27.887
And I won't have it!

35:27.970 --> 35:30.136
[Krakow] The backslapping.
The favor trading!

35:30.220 --> 35:32.679
You're supposed to be thinking
about the citizenry.

35:32.762 --> 35:33.929
Not your own pocket book!

35:34.011 --> 35:35.929
Oh, what the hell,
Secretary Krakow.

35:36.011 --> 35:37.845
I don't even carry
a pocket book.

35:37.929 --> 35:41.428
And you, Stan--
Take this down--

35:41.512 --> 35:43.929
I know who you paid off
for your seat,

35:44.011 --> 35:47.553
and I know who you're paying off
for your next one.

35:47.637 --> 35:49.303
And I'm not just gonna
sit here and--

35:49.387 --> 35:52.428
I'm not going down with
the ship, God damn it!

35:52.512 --> 35:53.679
You hear me?

35:53.762 --> 35:56.095
Because there is coronavirus
on it,

35:56.178 --> 35:59.053
and that shit spreads.

35:59.136 --> 36:03.303
And what the fuck
happened to trust, huh?

36:03.387 --> 36:07.011
I look around this table,
and I do not see friends.

36:07.095 --> 36:09.095
Whoa, what the fuck,
Jesus, Krakow.

36:09.178 --> 36:12.887
I won't be a part of
a criminal enterprise...

36:12.970 --> 36:15.679
I will not be part of
a criminal enterprise!

36:15.762 --> 36:20.470
I will not be a part of
a goddamn criminal enterprise!

36:20.553 --> 36:22.470
Hey.

36:22.553 --> 36:24.220
Hi.

36:27.345 --> 36:28.845
Quick drink
before we go?

36:28.929 --> 36:30.887
Yeah.
I'm gonna wash my hands.

36:31.720 --> 36:34.679
[cellphone vibrates]

36:34.762 --> 36:36.303
Where are you?

36:36.387 --> 36:37.720
[Wendy] Tanner's.

36:37.804 --> 36:39.637
Approved...

36:39.720 --> 36:41.387
Approved...

36:41.470 --> 36:44.136
Good. I want to know whether
he's made any progress or not.

36:44.220 --> 36:46.053
You should ask him.

36:46.136 --> 36:48.053
Right.
Do me a favor.

36:48.136 --> 36:50.387
Take some pictures of what
he's got, then send them to me.

36:52.720 --> 36:53.970
[scoffs]
You know what?

36:54.053 --> 36:55.220
I'm not doing that.

36:55.303 --> 36:57.095
It's a bad ask,
and I'm not playing.

36:57.178 --> 36:58.845
You're supposed to
help me harvest

36:58.929 --> 37:00.637
the most out of my people--
as I have been all day.

37:00.720 --> 37:03.095
[Axe] Their work product
is mine by extension--

37:03.178 --> 37:04.512
Except he's not
one of yours.

37:04.595 --> 37:07.053
Not like the rest.
So learn to wait.

37:07.136 --> 37:09.762
Or, again,
ask him yourself.

37:09.845 --> 37:11.470
♪ dramatic music  ♪

37:11.553 --> 37:12.970
God damn it--

37:13.053 --> 37:17.970
♪♪♪

37:18.053 --> 37:19.136
You good?

37:19.220 --> 37:20.679
All good.

37:20.762 --> 37:22.303
Cheers.
Cheers.

37:22.387 --> 37:26.970
♪♪♪

37:27.053 --> 37:28.845
How's it going?
Get everyone in the office yet?

37:28.929 --> 37:31.512
Only about 16 people
have donated so far...

37:31.595 --> 37:33.679
[sighs]

37:33.762 --> 37:35.804
Hey!
Let's go, everyone!

37:35.887 --> 37:37.220
Blood drive today!

37:37.303 --> 37:38.845
Roll up those sleeves
and get in there!

37:38.929 --> 37:41.762
Let's show the blood bank
that the hearts of NYAG

37:41.845 --> 37:44.095
are full of generosity!

37:44.178 --> 37:46.345
Don't think you all are exempt
because you're new.

37:46.428 --> 37:48.679
Get in there and give blood!

37:48.762 --> 37:50.595
♪ funky music  ♪

37:50.679 --> 37:52.929
Blood drive!
Ya bleed yet?

37:53.011 --> 37:54.553
Oh, I already gave.

37:54.637 --> 37:56.387
I give blood regularly,
actually.

37:56.470 --> 37:57.720
You're a true mensch.

37:57.804 --> 37:59.845
I like getting the juice box
at the end.

37:59.929 --> 38:02.553
Sometimes it's orange,
sometimes it is apple.

38:02.637 --> 38:04.011
They even give ya
a cookie sometimes

38:04.095 --> 38:06.428
if you know to ask for it.
[chuckles]

38:06.512 --> 38:07.845
You know what never changes,
though?

38:07.929 --> 38:10.220
What's that?
The amount of blood they draw.

38:10.303 --> 38:13.136
470 milliliters is
a little less than a pint.

38:13.220 --> 38:16.053
Your nurse in there
is taking 600.

38:16.136 --> 38:19.178
Busted.

38:19.261 --> 38:22.637
To borrow from
the Ray Charles songbook.

38:24.845 --> 38:27.345
Why do you want our blood,
Chuck?

38:27.428 --> 38:30.428
I didn't know if this fell
within our agreement,

38:30.512 --> 38:33.637
but hell,
everything should.

38:33.720 --> 38:37.637
Uh...

38:37.720 --> 38:40.136
My father.

38:40.220 --> 38:42.845
If I don't find him
a living kidney donor,

38:42.929 --> 38:46.762
he'll die before he reaches
the top of the waitlist.

38:46.845 --> 38:49.178
If I can even
get him on it.

38:49.261 --> 38:51.595
And if someone here
is a match?

38:51.679 --> 38:53.345
How would that
not be coercion,

38:53.428 --> 38:55.970
not to mention
a HIPAA violation?

38:56.053 --> 38:57.762
I will handle
the matter delicately.

38:57.845 --> 38:59.679
And indirectly.

38:59.762 --> 39:01.845
Hmm.

39:01.929 --> 39:03.720
You ever heard of
James Davenport?

39:03.804 --> 39:05.387
I don't believe so.

39:05.470 --> 39:06.512
No. Enlighten me.

39:06.595 --> 39:07.887
He was
an itinerant minister

39:08.011 --> 39:09.470
during the First
Great Awakening.

39:09.553 --> 39:12.136
Known for giving fiery,
passionate sermons.

39:12.220 --> 39:13.470
Developed
quite a following.

39:13.553 --> 39:16.345
One day, he was
preaching at a bonfire.

39:16.428 --> 39:18.720
He worked himself
into a frenzy.

39:18.804 --> 39:21.637
He started denouncing clothing
as a symbol of vanity.

39:21.720 --> 39:24.762
Took his own pants off
and threw them into the fire.

39:24.845 --> 39:26.345
Totally broke the spell--

39:26.428 --> 39:29.804
his congregants decided he'd
lost his mind and they left.

39:29.887 --> 39:31.637
You've got a devoted flock here,
Chuck,

39:31.720 --> 39:33.720
but you are getting
pretty close

39:33.804 --> 39:35.970
to throwing your pants
in the fire.

39:36.053 --> 39:39.637
♪♪♪

39:39.720 --> 39:41.679
[sighs]

39:41.762 --> 39:44.595
♪♪♪

39:44.679 --> 39:49.470
[Rian speaking Spanish]

39:49.553 --> 39:51.136
Where we at?

39:51.220 --> 39:53.011
We are on the verge!

39:53.095 --> 39:54.512
Of?
[Winston] Space and time.

39:54.595 --> 39:56.804
[Winston] Punching through
the envelope of pure profit.

39:56.887 --> 39:59.428
Axe is about to execute
a huge move--multi-sector play.

39:59.512 --> 40:01.428
Meteor minerals, geo-politics,
market makers.

40:01.512 --> 40:04.679
He's actually using
a me-developed trading tool!

40:04.762 --> 40:07.470
Already sold out of $3-plus
billion worth of crap to do it.

40:07.553 --> 40:11.970
And, more importantly,
today he finally saw me!

40:12.053 --> 40:14.095
He actually saw me!

40:14.178 --> 40:16.095
I need you to translate
what he is saying.

40:16.178 --> 40:17.178
Into Spanish?

40:17.261 --> 40:18.845
English first, please.

40:18.929 --> 40:20.679
Yeah, my head's in
another space.

40:20.762 --> 40:22.470
I've been gauging the situation
on the ground--

40:22.553 --> 40:24.178
talking to local officials,
scientists, diplomats.

40:24.261 --> 40:25.428
On the ground in...

40:25.512 --> 40:27.679
Chile.
I'm fluent in Spanish now.

40:27.762 --> 40:29.011
But no one
could really grasp

40:29.095 --> 40:31.053
the concepts
I was throwing at them.

40:31.136 --> 40:34.136
I must be too far ahead
cognitively.

40:34.220 --> 40:35.970
I have more than
a little Spanish.

40:36.053 --> 40:37.220
Give me a sample of
what you said.

40:37.303 --> 40:38.720
Yo quiero chilaquiles verdes

40:38.804 --> 40:40.136
en la biblioteca despacito,

40:40.220 --> 40:42.679
con un lado arroz.
Got it. Yep.

40:42.762 --> 40:44.679
What's that Tom Cruise says
in A Few Good Men?

40:44.762 --> 40:47.303
Yeah. Clear. Crystal.

40:47.387 --> 40:50.387
♪ dramatic music  ♪

40:50.470 --> 40:52.720
♪♪♪

40:52.804 --> 40:54.845
This drug is warping
your judgment.

40:54.929 --> 40:57.470
This isn't the Limitless  shit.
It's the Scarface  shit.

40:57.553 --> 40:59.428
No, no,
you're missing the train.

40:59.512 --> 41:02.720
Go see Victor, see if he has
any more, and then climb aboard.

41:02.804 --> 41:04.595
I could use another
supercomputer on the project.

41:04.679 --> 41:06.762
I'm thinking we trade the Asian
markets all night long--

41:06.845 --> 41:08.720
You've got to stop.
And ditch.

41:08.804 --> 41:10.887
My brilliant new analyst thinks
she's suddenly bilingual,

41:10.970 --> 41:12.387
but she just made
an elaborate lunch order

41:12.470 --> 41:13.887
on the phone with Chile.

41:13.970 --> 41:17.804
Of course.

41:17.887 --> 41:19.345
What else would you say?

41:19.428 --> 41:21.637
If it's not quant or impact,
you don't buy in.

41:21.720 --> 41:23.178
And that's if your motives
even check out

41:23.261 --> 41:25.553
in the first fucking place--
I see.

41:25.637 --> 41:27.178
I know you haven't been
completely sure about me,

41:27.261 --> 41:28.845
but ask yourself if
you can trust me now,

41:28.929 --> 41:30.303
because I'm telling you:

41:30.387 --> 41:32.261
It's likely the Socialists
win in Chile.

41:32.345 --> 41:33.553
So you lose
your government support

41:33.637 --> 41:35.387
for the planetary
mining base there.

41:35.470 --> 41:37.136
And if you don't let me put
your whole plan back in the box,

41:37.220 --> 41:39.720
and cancel your meteor play
before the trigger gets pulled,

41:39.804 --> 41:41.804
we're going to take
a massive loss. Fatal.

41:41.887 --> 41:44.261
God damn it...
Why are you messing with me?

41:44.345 --> 41:46.387
You trying to sabotage
the bigger play?

41:46.470 --> 41:47.720
Am I supposed to
trust you? How?

41:47.804 --> 41:50.345
Think about this:
You know financial loss

41:50.428 --> 41:52.261
and market inefficiency
and just plain error

41:52.345 --> 41:54.553
offend me more than almost
anything a human can do to me.

41:54.637 --> 41:56.345
If you listen to me,
and I'm fucking you over,

41:56.428 --> 41:58.136
you'll still have all that
capital you freed up.

41:58.220 --> 42:00.136
And you'll still be miles ahead
of the competition.

42:00.220 --> 42:01.261
So you can take
more of that stuff

42:01.345 --> 42:02.595
and come up with
your next plan,

42:02.679 --> 42:04.136
as well as kick my ass
out the door.

42:04.220 --> 42:06.095
But if I'm telling you
the truth, and you go ahead,

42:06.178 --> 42:08.970
you're gonna lose 3 billion
fucking dollars...

42:09.053 --> 42:12.470
♪♪♪

42:12.553 --> 42:16.136
♪♪♪

42:16.220 --> 42:18.595
And consider this:
success.

42:18.679 --> 42:21.261
Let's say you're right about
this whole crazy plan.

42:21.345 --> 42:22.512
You somehow pull it off

42:22.595 --> 42:25.136
and harvest more gold, platinum,
tungsten, and cobalt

42:25.220 --> 42:27.095
than the world has ever known...

42:27.178 --> 42:29.387
it will all end up
as worthless as sand,

42:29.470 --> 42:30.845
because it will
glut the market.

42:30.929 --> 42:33.220
Scarcity is the only thing
that gives that stuff value,

42:33.303 --> 42:36.512
and you will have fundamentally
destroyed that.

42:36.595 --> 42:39.011
Fuck.

42:39.095 --> 42:41.053
♪♪♪

42:41.136 --> 42:44.011
Pull the plug. Do it.

42:44.095 --> 42:48.553
♪♪♪

42:48.637 --> 42:51.095
Shut 'em down!
Shut down your Bloombergs

42:51.178 --> 42:53.345
and back away from
your keyboards immediately

42:53.428 --> 42:56.553
before we make any more stupid
fucking trades!

42:56.637 --> 43:01.178
♪♪♪

43:01.261 --> 43:05.887
♪♪♪

43:05.970 --> 43:10.470
♪♪♪

43:10.553 --> 43:14.929
♪♪♪

43:15.011 --> 43:16.720
All done, sir.
Mm.

43:16.804 --> 43:19.387
[nurse] Sorry to tell you, but
no one in the office is a match.

43:19.470 --> 43:21.470
But thanks for your donation
to the blood drive.

43:21.553 --> 43:23.011
It'll do a lot of good.

43:23.095 --> 43:24.637
[Chuck] Great.

43:24.720 --> 43:28.345
♪ dramatic music  ♪

43:28.428 --> 43:29.887
[sighs]

43:29.970 --> 43:34.762
♪♪♪

43:34.845 --> 43:39.512
♪♪♪

43:39.595 --> 43:44.095
♪♪♪

43:44.178 --> 43:47.387
[line ringing]

43:47.470 --> 43:48.929
You see the thing?

43:49.011 --> 43:51.345
The Krakow thing?
I just sent it to you.

43:51.428 --> 43:53.136
[indistinct shouting]

43:53.220 --> 43:55.261
I simply won't, I can't,
I'm not,

43:55.345 --> 43:58.512
part of a criminal enterprise.

43:58.595 --> 44:01.804
I expressed same,
and suddenly I'm bounced,

44:01.887 --> 44:03.929
[Krakow] which is fine, great!

44:04.011 --> 44:05.303
[Krakow] I'm done.

44:05.387 --> 44:06.679
Back to what I do best,

44:06.762 --> 44:10.762
making the ca-ching machine
go ca-ching.

44:10.845 --> 44:12.845
The man detonated
a suicide vest.

44:12.929 --> 44:14.470
Unless someone
put him up to it.

44:14.553 --> 44:16.512
Either way, he's out.
Fired by the White House.

44:16.595 --> 44:18.512
His whole slate's been spiked,
including--

44:18.595 --> 44:20.261
My national bank charter.

44:20.345 --> 44:23.679
God damn it.
Back to square fucking one.

44:25.720 --> 44:27.512
Get Victor on
reviving this.

44:27.595 --> 44:29.387
Give him all the resources
he needs.

44:29.470 --> 44:30.804
Tell him to think broadly.

44:30.887 --> 44:33.345
Use his Ivy League brain and
his Far Rockaway street smarts.

44:33.428 --> 44:34.595
And get me Wendy.

44:34.679 --> 44:36.470
Out.
For the night.

44:36.553 --> 44:38.428
Didn't come back
after her meetings.

44:38.512 --> 44:40.637
Oh. No. Sure.

44:40.720 --> 44:43.053
Important stuff.

44:47.762 --> 44:50.303
Maybe we can move a part
of her agenda forward.

44:50.387 --> 44:52.470
[elevator bell dings]

44:52.553 --> 44:54.428
Who are you?

44:54.512 --> 44:55.887
You must not watch
Rachael Ray.

44:55.970 --> 44:57.720
No.
You should.

44:57.804 --> 44:59.929
You're Mary Giuliani.
Axe sent me.

45:00.011 --> 45:01.428
I'm here to set up
for the viewing party.

45:01.512 --> 45:03.136
There is no
viewing party.

45:03.220 --> 45:05.470
No, Tanner,

45:05.553 --> 45:08.804
if Axe says there is,
there is...

45:08.887 --> 45:11.804
♪ dramatic music  ♪

45:11.887 --> 45:15.178
♪♪♪

45:15.261 --> 45:18.303
♪♪♪

45:18.387 --> 45:20.512
The question is:

45:20.595 --> 45:21.970
Will you be here for it?

45:22.053 --> 45:26.178
♪♪♪

45:26.261 --> 45:30.595
♪♪♪

45:30.679 --> 45:32.220
Knew you'd call.

45:32.303 --> 45:36.178
I just need your services to
get him past the medical workup.

45:36.261 --> 45:38.637
I can find the kidney
myself.

45:38.720 --> 45:41.345
Okay, Chuck.
It's your decision.

45:41.428 --> 45:43.720
But you're still gonna
have to pay full price.

45:43.804 --> 45:45.261
Sure thing.

45:45.345 --> 45:48.011
I already have.

45:49.095 --> 45:52.011
And this

45:52.095 --> 45:55.428
is 38K for that
little girl, Pete.

45:55.512 --> 45:57.845
I trust you to see
she gets it

45:57.929 --> 46:01.011
and keeps her full
complement of organs.

46:01.095 --> 46:02.136
Sure thing.

46:02.220 --> 46:03.512
Whatever you say,
boss.

46:03.595 --> 46:05.220
I gotta kill the deal
for her spleen?

46:05.303 --> 46:06.887
Yes.
Okay.

46:06.970 --> 46:09.804
You can start working your magic
with my father now.

46:11.136 --> 46:12.970
[Chuck] Dad,
we're ready for you!

46:13.053 --> 46:15.011
[indistinct conversations]

46:15.095 --> 46:18.637
♪ jazz music  ♪

46:18.720 --> 46:19.595
Thanks, Mary.

46:19.679 --> 46:20.595
Thanks, Axe.

46:20.679 --> 46:23.011
♪♪♪

46:23.095 --> 46:25.720
Hey. DJ D-Sol,

46:25.804 --> 46:29.011
so, come on, how about selling
me a piece of your bank?

46:29.095 --> 46:31.887
I'm really sorry, but Marcus
isn't for sale at any price.

46:31.970 --> 46:34.720
Really? Lasry, you want to talk
some sense into him?

46:34.804 --> 46:37.595
I wish I could, but he's not
changing his mind.

46:37.679 --> 46:39.387
Sorry.
Sorry, Axe.

46:39.470 --> 46:40.887
Alright, guys.
Well, enjoy the show.

46:40.970 --> 46:42.595
Thanks for coming.
Good to see you.

46:42.679 --> 46:44.220
Thanks for having us.
Have a good one.

46:44.303 --> 46:45.428
Alright.

46:45.512 --> 46:47.804
[indistinct conversations]

46:47.887 --> 46:49.804
C.C., what's up, man?
How you doing, Axe?

46:49.887 --> 46:51.178
Glad you're here.
Thanks. Thanks for having me.

46:51.261 --> 46:52.637
I like what I see.
Yeah, it's good, huh?

46:52.720 --> 46:54.178
Check this out.
Weird shit.

46:54.261 --> 46:56.136
I think you'll like it.

46:59.553 --> 47:00.887
You enjoying yourself?

47:00.970 --> 47:03.053
Oh, yes, very much.
But you were right.

47:03.136 --> 47:06.345
Pictures on a phone would not
have done these justice.

47:06.428 --> 47:10.679
And yet somehow it feels like
a party for one.

47:10.762 --> 47:12.595
Well, your artist
seems to be

47:12.679 --> 47:14.970
handling the situation
very well.

47:15.053 --> 47:17.470
Well, he's making the best of it
because he has to.

47:17.553 --> 47:19.595
And because
he's a professional.

47:19.679 --> 47:23.261
Oh. He is the real deal,
isn't he?

47:23.345 --> 47:25.887
You should try the canapés.
They're delicious.

47:25.970 --> 47:29.637
[indistinct conversations]

47:29.720 --> 47:32.011
♪ up-tempo music  ♪

47:32.095 --> 47:34.845
I love the composition,
the world of this painting.

47:34.929 --> 47:38.303
You seem like
you're holding up.

47:38.387 --> 47:40.762
You know,
maybe Axe is right.

47:40.845 --> 47:42.303
He owns it all.

47:42.387 --> 47:43.679
He's keeping me fresh.

47:43.762 --> 47:46.512
He's trying to push me
to go further.

47:46.595 --> 47:48.303
That's generous.
Yeah.

47:48.387 --> 47:51.011
Tanner, these pieces
are stunning,

47:51.095 --> 47:52.929
even in their raw form.

47:53.011 --> 47:54.762
Well, thank you.

47:54.845 --> 47:57.637
How impasto
will you go?

47:57.720 --> 48:01.178
I studied art history
back in college.

48:01.261 --> 48:03.095
♪♪♪

48:03.178 --> 48:08.053
My husband--ex-husband--
has a fund.

48:08.136 --> 48:10.553
I did very well
in the divorce.

48:10.637 --> 48:12.303
I'm a bit of a collector.

48:12.387 --> 48:14.345
I can see that.
Yeah.

48:14.428 --> 48:16.845
Which one of the pieces
inspires you?

48:16.929 --> 48:18.553
[chuckles]

48:18.637 --> 48:20.261
I love this one.

48:20.345 --> 48:22.178
And why is that?

48:22.261 --> 48:24.220
It's about growth,

48:24.303 --> 48:25.512
the tenacity of life.

48:25.595 --> 48:28.929
The universality of biology.

48:29.011 --> 48:31.387
The birth-death cycle.

48:31.470 --> 48:35.887
Your work
is so understated.

48:35.970 --> 48:39.929
It invites you to
stop and look again.

48:40.011 --> 48:43.679
Or else you might miss
the significance.

48:43.762 --> 48:45.720
I'm not sure
subjecting the artist

48:45.804 --> 48:48.011
to some dime-store
interpretation is the way to--

48:48.095 --> 48:49.637
Sometimes.

48:49.720 --> 48:52.595
But sometimes you
find someone who--

48:52.679 --> 48:55.220
who has an eye,
who gets it.

48:55.303 --> 48:56.929
What else do you see?

48:57.011 --> 48:59.595
♪♪♪

48:59.679 --> 49:01.553
I see passion.

49:01.637 --> 49:03.345
[speaking indistinctly]

49:03.428 --> 49:07.428
♪♪♪

49:07.512 --> 49:11.553
♪♪♪

49:11.637 --> 49:15.679
♪♪♪

49:15.762 --> 49:18.512
Absolutely
incorruptible.

49:18.595 --> 49:21.845
Unless you're a socialite with
a nine-figure bank account

49:21.929 --> 49:24.387
with a sweet tooth
for abstract art.

49:24.470 --> 49:29.220
♪♪♪

49:29.303 --> 49:34.261
♪♪♪

49:34.345 --> 49:37.887
That went about
as expected.

49:37.970 --> 49:39.762
The admixture of
art and commerce,

49:39.845 --> 49:42.387
almost as intoxicating
as whiskey and water.

49:42.470 --> 49:45.679
And almost twice as likely
to cause bar fights.

49:48.345 --> 49:50.720
What could be solved
has been solved.

49:50.804 --> 49:52.679
Which is most of it.

49:52.762 --> 49:54.595
There will be cap-gains exposure
from the sell-offs.

49:54.679 --> 49:55.762
We'll manage that
by rolling back

49:55.845 --> 49:57.637
into new, more earthbound,
positions.

49:57.720 --> 50:00.595
Thank you for the sanity
and competence.

50:00.679 --> 50:03.762
A non-intoxicating yet
utterly essential pairing.

50:03.845 --> 50:05.553
And hardly any bar fights.

50:05.637 --> 50:07.220
I have had one,
you know.

50:07.303 --> 50:08.637
Bar fight?

50:08.720 --> 50:10.387
It was just after seeing
Y Tu Mamá También.

50:10.470 --> 50:12.053
In a theater.
I was all hopped up,

50:12.136 --> 50:14.095
and some kid--
Willard Broxton--

50:14.178 --> 50:16.637
from my high school went into
his usual routine,

50:16.720 --> 50:18.804
ripping into me.
And I just decided, not today.

50:18.887 --> 50:20.095
Did you throw
the first punch?

50:20.178 --> 50:21.637
The only punch, yes.

50:21.720 --> 50:23.887
And swore never again to
give in to that emotion.

50:23.970 --> 50:25.470
I also haven't watched
that movie again

50:25.553 --> 50:26.720
for fear of what
it might provoke.

50:26.804 --> 50:28.553
Like Axe
and Magnum Force!

50:28.637 --> 50:31.178
Yeah.
But tell me.

50:31.261 --> 50:34.387
You don't usually traffic in
tales of pugilism and cinema.

50:34.470 --> 50:35.387
Something
you want to say?

50:35.470 --> 50:37.261
There is. Yes.

50:37.345 --> 50:39.720
You will see a loss from
Mase Carbon on the books today.

50:39.804 --> 50:41.095
It will grow.

50:41.178 --> 50:44.011
[sniffs]
Those are fighting words.

50:44.095 --> 50:45.637
Was it because you had to
look after our shop?

50:45.720 --> 50:47.804
No. I can't blame Vigilantrix
for this.

50:47.887 --> 50:49.929
And the loss isn't
a one-time thing.

50:50.011 --> 50:51.178
We are going to carry it
for a while.

50:51.261 --> 50:52.553
Prince and I
put our heads together

50:52.637 --> 50:54.136
on the impact scandal--
Prince?!

50:54.220 --> 50:55.845
Wendy and I made a calculated
risk to work with him

50:55.929 --> 50:57.887
because there was real
long-term upside.

50:57.970 --> 51:00.345
You mis-fucking-calculated.
What happened?

51:00.428 --> 51:02.345
Prince convinced me
to take the short-term hit

51:02.428 --> 51:04.095
in order to rebuild
Shine-Lucence publicly

51:04.178 --> 51:06.136
and preserve the pristine
reputation of Mase Carbon--

51:06.220 --> 51:07.679
actually, that's not strictly
what happened.

51:07.762 --> 51:09.720
I volunteered.
No, you didn't.

51:09.804 --> 51:11.595
Even if you think
you did.

51:11.679 --> 51:14.178
Yeah, and if you did,

51:14.261 --> 51:16.011
it's 'cause
he wanted you to.

51:16.095 --> 51:17.762
Tell it.
That's not how it happened.

51:17.845 --> 51:19.720
I think maybe the half-life
of that Vigilantrix

51:19.804 --> 51:20.637
is making you angsty.

51:20.720 --> 51:22.095
Nope. Born this way.

51:22.178 --> 51:23.428
Stoked it. Intentionally.

51:23.512 --> 51:24.887
I preserve it.
I know.

51:24.970 --> 51:27.595
But Prince: He almost ate
the entire loss himself,

51:27.679 --> 51:29.303
to buy me out of
the company.

51:29.387 --> 51:30.970
But then I saw the sagacity
in his plan, and I insisted--

51:31.053 --> 51:33.303
Textbook fucking
manipulation.

51:33.387 --> 51:35.553
He played you.
And me by extension.

51:35.637 --> 51:37.136
He duped you into
taking that loss.

51:37.220 --> 51:39.553
And now that's on
my fucking sheet.

51:39.637 --> 51:42.720
I bet he'd already
pared his position

51:42.804 --> 51:46.595
before all this going public
with the story bullshit started.

51:46.679 --> 51:48.553
Sounds to me like
an act of war.

51:48.637 --> 51:50.261
Sounds that way
because it is that way.

51:50.345 --> 51:51.887
Mm.
You know what?

51:51.970 --> 51:54.303
That fucker made me believe
he was laying down--

51:54.387 --> 51:56.053
no, of course not.

51:56.136 --> 51:58.261
The ol' sneak attack
from behind.

51:58.345 --> 52:01.512
Is there anything I can say to
get you to see it differently?

52:01.595 --> 52:03.303
There is not.

52:11.220 --> 52:13.178
Wags.

52:13.261 --> 52:15.762
You ready to become a wartime
consiglieri once again?

52:15.845 --> 52:18.428
Pop had Genco.
You have me.

52:18.512 --> 52:20.428
You know why they called it
going to the mattresses

52:20.512 --> 52:22.136
when mob families
went to war?

52:22.220 --> 52:23.929
It's mentioned in 1
but never explained.

52:24.011 --> 52:25.220
General idea.

52:25.303 --> 52:27.095
It's because you had to
move out of your home

52:27.178 --> 52:30.595
and hole up someplace where
no one could find you,

52:30.679 --> 52:32.053
with all your men.

52:32.136 --> 52:33.637
But you had to do it quick,

52:33.720 --> 52:35.679
so that you'd get the jump
on the rival family

52:35.762 --> 52:37.136
before they got
the jump on you.

52:37.220 --> 52:39.053
So you had places
stashed around the city,

52:39.136 --> 52:41.011
with the mattresses
on the floor.

52:41.095 --> 52:43.470
And that is where
you would make your stand

52:43.553 --> 52:46.428
until you nailed the boss
of the rival family.

52:46.512 --> 52:48.261
And once you got him

52:48.345 --> 52:50.428
and all his soldiers
fell into line,

52:50.512 --> 52:52.470
that's when you'd go home
to your comfy bed

52:52.553 --> 52:54.220
and your wife and kids.

52:54.303 --> 52:55.595
And that's what
we're about to do?

52:55.679 --> 52:57.095
We sure are.

52:57.178 --> 52:58.261
Get me Bach.

52:58.345 --> 52:59.595
Get me Hall.

52:59.679 --> 53:01.595
Get me anyone
who can help us find out

53:01.679 --> 53:05.512
what is near and dear to
Michael Thomas Aquinas Prince.

53:05.595 --> 53:08.095
Because when I find out
what matters to him,

53:08.178 --> 53:10.637
I am going to
fucking destroy it.

53:10.720 --> 53:13.512
And him right along
with it.

53:13.595 --> 53:15.887
♪ Shit outta luck  ♪

53:15.970 --> 53:18.679
♪ Hardwired to self-destruct  ♪

53:18.762 --> 53:20.970
♪♪♪

53:21.053 --> 53:23.136
♪ Go  ♪

53:23.220 --> 53:26.762
♪♪♪

53:26.845 --> 53:30.595
♪♪♪

53:30.679 --> 53:34.136
♪♪♪

53:34.220 --> 53:36.512
♪ On the way to paranoia  ♪

53:36.595 --> 53:38.970
♪ On the crooked borderline  ♪

53:39.053 --> 53:41.637
♪ On the way to
great destroyer  ♪

53:41.720 --> 53:43.428
♪ Doom design  ♪

53:43.512 --> 53:45.470
♪ We're so fucked  ♪

53:45.553 --> 53:48.345
